In the *Hitachi no Kuni Fudoki*, Omi Sayama no Mikoto is associated with the origin of the sacred boat ritual of {{ill|Kashima Shrine|ja|鹿島神宮|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kashima Shrine|qq=}}. During the reign of {{ill|Emperor Keikō|ja|景行天皇|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Keikō|qq=}}, the deity {{ill|Takemikazuchi|ja|武甕槌命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takemikazuchi|qq=}} instructed Omi Sayama no Mikoto to prepare a sacred boat. Following the divine instructions, he constructed three new boats over two jō (about 6 meters) in length and offered them to the emperor. The text describes a mystical encounter in which the boat appeared alternately on land and sea, reinforcing his reverence for the deity.
